{
  "text": "Well-marked rhythmic beats require the execution of defined body movements, usually augmenting or isolating some body parts. This demands from the dancer body awareness and trunk mobility [CITATION_1] , preventing complications and deterioration of his or her health status [CITATION_2] . Rhythmic alternation suggests that movements are executed repetitively, which benefits motor learning and reduces spasticity [CITATION_3] . The movements of the trunk and lower and upper limbs can be trained separately to be executed simultaneously and continuously, in a coordinated way and synchronized with the rhythm [CITATION_4] .",
